            }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`console`}</inlineCode>{` sink`}</a>{`:`}</p>
          <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
              "className": "language-toml",
              "metastring": "title=\"vector.toml\"",
              "title": "\"vector.toml\""
            }}>{`[sources.foo]
  type = "stdin"

[sinks.bar]
  inputs = ["foo"]
  type = "console"
  encoding.codec = "text"
`}</code></pre>
          <CodeExplanation mdxType="CodeExplanation">
            <ul>
              <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<a parentName="li" {...{
                  "href": "/docs/reference/sources/stdin/"
                }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`stdin`}</inlineCode>{` source`}</a>{` tells Vector to receive data over `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`STDIN`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</li>
              <li parentName="ul">{`The `}{`[`}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`console`}</inlineCode>{` source]`}{`docs.sinks.stdout] tells Vector to simply print the data to `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`STDOUT`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</li>
              <li parentName="ul">{`The  `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`encoding.codec`}</inlineCode>{` tells Vector to print the data as plain text (unencoded).`}</li>
            </ul>
          </CodeExplanation>
          <p>{`Every component within a Vector config has an identifier chosen by you. This
allows you to specify where a sink should gather its data from (using the
`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`inputs`}</inlineCode>{` field).`}</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3 {...{
            "id": "hello-world"
          }}>{`Hello World!`}</h3>
          <p>{`That's it for our first config, now pipe an event through it:`}</p>
          <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
              "className": "language-bash"
            }}>{`echo 'Hello World!' | vector --config ./vector.toml
`}</code></pre>
